  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large pot over medium heat.",
    "Add diced onion and minced garlic and sauté until fragrant, about 3 minutes.",
    "Stir in diced cassava, sliced carrot, and fermented cabbage and cook for 5 minutes.",
    "Pour in vegetable broth, add bay leaf, thyme, sea salt, and pepper, and bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer until cassava is tender, about 20 minutes.",
    "Stir in chopped kale and cook for an additional 3 minutes until wilted.",
    "Remove bay leaf, taste, and adjust seasoning if needed.",
    "Serve hot, optionally with a drizzle of cashew cream for extra richness."
